    dc:creator "Herbert, David G." ;
    dc:date "2024" ;
    dc:title "The Vetigastropoda (Mollusca) of Walters Shoal, with descriptions of two new genera and thirty new species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10727854>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10727861>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10727857> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10727854>
    dc:description "Fig. 38. A–B. Calliostoma pantopunctatum sp. nov., holotype, living animal, shell diameter 5.8 mm (MNHN-IM-2013-67275). C–E. Kaiparathina monticola sp. nov., holotype, living animal, anterolateral structure arrowed, shell diameter 6.8 mm (MNHN-IM-2013-67168). F. Stomatella multilirata sp. nov., Walters Shoal, stn WS03, greatest shell dimension 6.0 mm (MNHN). Images courtesy of Alain Barrère/ MNHN." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10727854/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10727861>
    dc:description "Fig. 40. Kaiparathina monticola sp. nov. A–C. Paratypes (MNHN-IM-2000-35726). A. Oblique view of apex. B. Sculptural detail of protoconch. C. Basal view of juvenile showing lack of spiral lirae. D–G. Jaw and radula (paratype, MNHN-IM-2013-67260). D. Ventral (inner) surface of jaw, anterior edge below. E. Detail of jaw structure. F. Radula, entire width. G. Radula, detail of rachidian, lateral and inner marginal teeth. Scale bars: A, D =200 μm; B, F = 100 μm; C=1.0 mm; E, G =50 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10727861/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10727857>
    dc:description "Fig. 39. Kaiparathina monticola sp. nov. A. Holotype, diameter 6.8 mm (MNHN-IM-2013-67168). B. Specimen with zig-zag colour pattern, diameter 6.0 mm (paratype, MNHN-IM-2000-35726). C–F. Live-taken specimen with blotched colour pattern, diameter 6.4 mm (paratype, MNHN- IM-2000-35727)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10727857/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

